{"body": "T P -1. D.C-V (2025-12) 1 of 2\nT\n\nTax Credit for Childcare Expenses\n\nSCHEDULE\n\nC\n\nIf you and your spouse on December 31, 2025, are both entering an amount on line 455 of your respective returns, you must each file your own Schedule C.\nTo qualify for the tax credit, the childcare expenses paid must have been incurred while you or your spouse on December 31, 2025, was in any\nof the situations listed below.\nCheck the applicable box or boxes. You or your spouse was:\n\n• carrying out the duties of an office or employment \b���������������������������������������������������\n• carrying on a business alone or as a partner actively engaged in the business \b�����������������\n\n• practising a profession \b���������������������������������������������������������������������������������������\n• carrying out research under a grant \b�����������������������������������������������������������������������\n\n10\n11\n12\n13\n\n• actively seeking employment \b�������������������������������������������������������������������������������\n\n14\n\n• attending a secondary school or taking a course remotely or in person at a qualified\neducational institution on a full-time basis (see line 455 in the guide) \b���������������������������\n\n15\n\n• attending a secondary school or taking a course remotely or in person at a qualified\neducational institution on a part-time basis (see line 455 in the guide) \b���������������������������\n\n16\n\n• receiving benefits under the Québec parental insurance plan (QPIP) or benefits related\nto a birth or adoption under the Employment Insurance plan \b���������������������������������������\n\n17\n\nA\n1\n\nEligible child\nA child under 16 at some point in the year or\na child of any age with a mental or physical\ninfirmity who was your or your spouse’s\ndependant.\nAn eligible child can be:\n• your or your spouse’s child; or\n• a child who was your or your spouse’s\ndependant and whose income for the year\nwas not more than $13,658 (the child’s\nincome is the amount on line 275 of their\nincome tax return or the amount that would\nhave been entered on line 275 had the child\nfiled a return).\n\nChildcare expenses qualifying for the tax credit\nInformation about each eligible child (see the definition above)\nA – First and last name\n\nB – Relationship to you\n\nC – Child’s net income\n\n1\n\n1\n\n1\n\n2\n\n2\n\n2\n\n3\n\n3\n\n3\n\n4\n\n4\n\n4\n\n5\n\n5\n\n5\n\n6\n\n6\n\n6\n\n2\n\nChildcare expenses paid\nDate of birth\n\nChild’s first name\n\nY\n\nY\n\nY\n\nY\n\nM\n\nM\n\nD\n\nD\n\nChildcare expenses that qualify\nfor the tax credit (box E of the\nRL-24 slip) or amount on the receipt\n\nIdentification number (box H of the RL-24 slip),\nor social insurance number\nof the person who received the payments\n\n26.3\n\n26\n\n26.1\n\n26.2\n\n27.3\n\n27\n\n27.2\n\n28.3\n\n28\n\n29.3\n\n29\n\n30.3\n\n30\n\n31.3\n\n31\n\n32.3\n\n32\n\n33.3\n\n33\n\n34.3\n\n34\n\n35.3\n\n35\n\n36.3\n\n36\n\n37.3\n\n37\n\n+ 27.1\n+ 28.1\n+ 29.1\n+ 30.1\n+ 31.1\n+ 32.1\n+ 33.1\n+ 34.1\n+ 35.1\n+ 36.1\n+ 37.1\n\n28.2\n29.2\n30.2\n31.2\n32.2\n33.2\n34.2\n35.2\n36.2\n37.2\n\nTotal expenses that you could not enter on lines 26.1 through 37.1 because\nthere was not enough space.\nComplete section 2 of Part A of another copy of this schedule and enter the amount\nfrom line 39. Schedule C is available at revenuquebec.ca.\n+ 38.1\nAdd lines 26.1 through 38.1.\n= 39\nAllowance for or reimbursement of childcare expenses shown in box 201\nof the RL-1 slip or in box J of the RL-5 slip, if the expenses are included on line 39 – 40\nSubtract line 40 from line 39.\n\b\nChildcare expenses qualifying for the tax credit = 41\nContinued on the next page.\nEnclose this schedule with your return.\nIf you want to keep a copy for your records, see the guide.\n\nY4C1 ZZ 89526749\n\nPrescribed form\n\nC\n\nT\n\nB\n\nChildcare expense limit\n\nNumber of eligible children listed in Part A (lines 1 through 6):\n• who have a severe and prolonged impairment in mental or physical functions,\nregardless of age\n• who were born after December 31, 2018,\nother than those covered on line 42 above\n• who were born after December 31, 2008, or who have an infirmity,\nother than those covered on lines 42 and 44 above\nAdd lines 43, 45 and 47.\n\b\n\nC\n\n42\n\n×\n\n$16,800\n\n43\n\n44\n\n×\n\n$12,275\n\n45\n\n46\n\n×\n\n$6,180\n\n47\n\nChildcare expense limit = 50\n\nFamily income\n\nAmount from line 275 of your return\n\n76\n\nAmount from line 275 of your spouse’s return (spouse on December 31, 2025)\nAdd lines 76 and 78.\n\b\n\nD\n\nT P -1. D.C-V (2025-12) 2 of 2\n\n+ 78\nFamily income = 80\n\nTax credit for childcare expenses\n\nAmount from line 41 or line 50, whichever is less\n\n85\n\n× 92\n\nTax credit rate based on family income (line 80 above). Refer to the table below.\nMultiply line 85 by line 92.\n\n= 94\n\nAmount your spouse on December 31, 2025, is claiming on line 455 of their return\nSubtract line 96 from line 94.\nCarry the result to line 455 of your return.\b\n\n– 96\n\nIf you would like to receive the tax shield, check box 99.\nSee the eligibility requirements at line 460 in the guide.\n\n%\n\nTax credit for childcare expenses = 98\n\n\b����������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������\n\n99\n\nTax credit rates\nUse this table to determine the tax credit rate that corresponds to your family income (line 80) and carry the rate to line 92 above. If the amount\non line 80 is 0, enter 78% on line 92.\nTax rate based on family income\nFamily income\nmore than\n\nnot more than\n\nTax credit\n\n$0\n\n$24,795\n\n78%\n\n$24,795\n\n$43,725\n\n75%\n\n$43,725\n\n$45,340\n\n74%\n\n$45,340\n\n$46,970\n\n73%\n\n$46,970\n\n$48,570\n\n72%\n\n$48,570\n\n$50,195\n\n71%\n\n$50,195\n\n$119,835\n\n70%\n\n$119,835\n\nor more\n\n67%\n\nEnclose this schedule with your return.\nIf you want to keep a copy for your records, see the guide.\n\nY4C2 ZZ 